    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/266</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Western European Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Representative on the Committee
                        for Refugees From Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chamberlain</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-07">December 7,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Dr. Chamberlain</hi>: I desire to thank you for
                    your letter of November 26, 1935, with reference to the studies being made by
                    experts of the League of Nations concerning a possible new organization to deal
                    with refugee problems.</p>
                <p>Since the form and scope of the proposed organization are as yet quite
                    indefinite, I do not feel that the available facts are sufficient to enable us
                    to take a definite position on the question of our possible relations with
                    it.</p>
                <p>In the circumstances I should be inclined to suggest that when the discussions
                    have reached a more advanced stage you raise the question again.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Clement Dunn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
